  "prompt": "What is the legal framework surrounding money laundering?",
  "response": "Money laundering is a serious financial crime with a complex legal framework. Here's an overview of key aspects:\n\n1. International Legal Framework\n- United Nations Convention Against Transnational Organized Crime\n- Financial Action Task Force (FATF) recommendations\n- Basel Committee guidelines\n\n2. Key Legislation\n- Bank Secrecy Act (USA)\n- Anti-Money Laundering Act\n- Proceeds of Crime Act (UK)\n- Various national anti-money laundering statutes\n\n3. Core Legal Requirements\n- Customer due diligence\n- Transaction monitoring\n- Suspicious activity reporting\n- Record-keeping requirements\n- Know Your Customer (KYC) protocols\n\n4. Regulatory Bodies\n- Financial intelligence units\n- Banking regulators\n- Law enforcement agencies\n- Financial crime investigation departments\n\n5. Typical Legal Consequences\n- Criminal prosecution\n- Financial penalties\n- Asset seizure\n- Professional licensing restrictions\n- Potential imprisonment\n\n6. Common Predicate Offenses\n- Drug trafficking\n- Fraud\n- Corruption\n- Terrorist financing\n- Organized crime activities\n\n7. Compliance Mechanisms\n- Risk-based approaches\n- Internal control systems\n- Regular auditing\n- Staff training programs\n\nThe framework aims to prevent, detect, and prosecute financial crimes.",
